# Windows batch scripts must keep CRLF line endings. CMD.exe's label
# lookup (call :label) misbehaves on LF-only files when the script
# grows past a certain size, silently skipping tshark start/stop and
# producing the symptom seen in issue #15 (commit capture label not
# found). Store the raw bytes without any LF<->CRLF conversion so the
# file served by git clone, GitHub's "Download ZIP", and GitHub's raw
# view is always CRLF.
*.bat -text
